# docs:regen output (npm run docs:regen). Both use literal `*` for wildcard
# route/glob notation in markdown tables (e.g. `/api/admin/*`) -- Prettier's
# markdown formatter misreads a lone trailing `*` as an unmatched emphasis
# marker and "normalizes" it, silently turning some into `/api/admin/_`
# (wrong character, not just re-styled) and others into `/api/admin/\*`
# (escaped, at least visually equivalent but still not what the generator
# emits). Regenerate via docs:regen, don't hand-format.
docs/generated/DATA_MODEL.md
docs/generated/ENDPOINTS.md

# Not generated, but hits a related Prettier markdown defect: CommonMark
# disallows intraword emphasis for `_` specifically so identifiers like
# `head_coach` don't get misread as `_coach_`, but this file has real
# `_emphasis_` right next to snake_case identifiers (`team_member_roles`,
# `head_coach`, `sc_coach`) and Prettier's formatter got confused --
# `head_coach/sc_coach/physio` became `head*coach/sc_coach/physio` (only the
# FIRST underscore flipped) and `their _own_ report` became
# `their \_own* report` (escaped-open + stray-close, breaks the emphasis
# entirely). Caught 2026-07-17 diffing word-for-word against HEAD; reverted
# and excluded rather than hand-fix, since the same ambiguous adjacency
# recurs throughout this file as it grows.
docs/SOURCE_OF_TRUTH.md

